.TH AXT-DOC 1
.SH NAME
axt-doc \- diagnose local development environment issues
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B axt-doc
[\fIFLAGS\fR] which \fICMD\fR [--timeout \fIDURATION\fR]
.br
.B axt-doc
[\fIFLAGS\fR] \fICMD\fR
.br
.B axt-doc
[\fIFLAGS\fR] path
.br
.B axt-doc
[\fIFLAGS\fR] env
.br
.B axt-doc
[\fIFLAGS\fR] all \fICMD\fR [--timeout \fIDURATION\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B axt-doc
checks command resolution, PATH health, suspicious environment variables, and
secret-like environment variables without making network calls.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --show-secrets
Print secret-like environment variable values. Values are redacted by default.
.TP
.B --timeout \fIDURATION\fR
Limit version probing for subcommands that execute a local command.
.SH OUTPUT
Supports human, --json, and --agent. JSON emits schema axt.doc.v1. Agent mode emits summary-first JSONL.
.SH SECURITY
Secret-like names such as TOKEN, SECRET, KEY, PASSWORD, CREDENTIAL, PRIVATE, and
AUTH variants are redacted unless --show-secrets is explicitly passed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
axt-doc which cargo --json
axt-doc path --agent
axt-doc all rustc
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR axt-peek (1),
.BR axt-run (1)
